title: Emmaus golf team loses to St. Joseph's Prep in PIAA East Subregional
text:
Max Harrington shot a 2-over-par 74 for the Emmaus golf team on Friday (lehighvalleylive.com file photo) By Karl Gilbert | lehighvalleylive.com View/Post Comments 
Emmaus High School's golf team lost 302-319 to District 12 power St. Joseph's Prep in a PIAA Class AAA East Subregional Friday afternoon at Lulu Country Club in Glenside, Pa. 
St. Joseph's Prep, the defending state champion, has won four District 12 titles in the past seven years. 
Emmaus was led by senior Max Harrington (2-over-par 74), and junior Samantha Fritzinger , who shot 79. Harrington and Fritzinger won the boys and girls District 11 AAA titles, respectively, last Monday at Schuylkill Country Club. 
This season, the Green Hornets won their second consecutive Eastern Pennsylvania Conference championship with a 15-0 regular-season record, earned their fourth league title in a row, and captured a third straight District 11 Class AAA team championship. 
"Before the season, I would have been happy with any championship, but to win the league and district is great," said Emmaus coach Mike Mihalik (seventh year), the 2015 lehighvalleylive Golf Coach of the Year. "Max and Kevin won four league and three district championships. That's a great way end to their careers." 
St. Joseph's Prep advanced to the PIAA Class AAA Team Championships to be played Wednesday, October 28 at Heritage Hills Golf Resort and Conference Center in York, PA. AAA Subregional St. Joseph's Prep 302 -- Jack Mitchell 72, Mike Burns 74, Alex Butler 77, Andrew Gallagher 79. Emmaus 319 -- Max Harrington 74, Samantha Fritzinger 79, Kevin Caverly 81, Eric Cichocki 85.Played at Lulu Country Club.
